DOC.brief_summary: The objective study compare visual outcome three aspheric monofocal intraocular lens cataract surgery - ACRYSOF® IQ , Tecnis® Akreos® MI60 .
DOC.brief_title: Visual Outcome Visual Quality After Bilateral Implantation AcrySof® IQ IOL Compared MI60® Tecnis® IOL
DOC.criteria: Male female subject , age 50 . Subjects diagnose bilateral cataract require cataract extraction implantation posterior chamber intraocular lens . Subjects must willing undertake additional ophthalmic test within 3 month second lens implantation . Subjects must assess able dilate minimum 6 mm pre operatively . Subjects ' pupil size must ≥ 4.5 mm mesopic condition . Subjects previously corneal surgery . Subjects potential visual acuity < 6/12 due ocular pathology Subjects corneal pathology . Subjects astigmatism great 1D . Subjects diagnose glaucoma . Subjects diagnose diabetes . Subjects previously participate clinical investigation within 30 day prior enrolment Subjects know history poor compliance Subjects plan adjunctive surgery
